el like having breakfast the next day, thats just how filling this stuff is. They have a nice beer/ wine selection and there is nothing like a huge Sapporo beer to go with your ramen. They offer huge bottles! The service was really fast and friendly. We didn't feel rushed at all though. We where able to enjoy our ramen at a reasonable rate, drink our beer, as well as kick back relax and chat. I recommend you come here ready to eat. Also don't let the line deter you, its not as bad as you think besides Daikokuya is worth it! PS. If you do want to wait inside, you can. They have a cute section with comics at the front of the restaurant, with a cute kitschy decor.
