Wow. This place has a lot of reviews. Okay, before I get on with the good stuff, let's get rid of the bad. Yes, there's a long wait. However, there's a nice shopping center across the street. Go kill some time by looking at the Japanese fare up for sale and then come back! But I'm reviewing the food and not the faults of the establishment, although I will concede it would be awesome if Daikokuya owned that whole block for their restaurant space. So let's start with my order, which was a small tuna sashimi bowl combo! I say it that way because it's my favorite hands down. I don't think I'll be ordering anything else. That said, let's start with the salad. The portion is good as not to spoil your appetite considering it's somewhat of an anti-salad as it's pretty unhealthy, but oh-so-effing delicious. It's a magical experience everything it hits the lips. Then, the waitress brings out a small bowl of tuna sashimi blanketing some of the best rice I've tasted in the sushi world. The rice is pleasantly sweet and balanced with a tart finish. The sashimi portions are generous and taste great! The fish isn't rubbery, mushy, nor bland. Now for the main event! The ramen. Echoing the many sentiments found throughout this page for Daikokuya, the best ramen I've had. I lived in Seattle, and currently live in O.C. Better than any ramen I've had in the international district in Seattle (Samurai Noodle) and better than Shin-sen-gumi & Men-tatsu in Costa Mesa. Did I mention that Daikokuya is better by far? Everything about it is so good. The broth is heavy I admit, but the flavor is all there. How else are you going to pack all that flavor in there?! It's very savory, complex, and meant to please; the noodles are fresh and of the perfect consistency; the egg offers a nice balance of texture along with the bamboo shoots. When everything is said and done, my bowls are empty. ALL OF THEM. It's a lot of food for the money by the way. So, it offers a one, two, three punch for the taste buds. T.K.O. My taste buds are knocked out and are now in heaven. Extras ordered - Diet coke. Pictures added! Look for the HK images logo. In summary... Service - 10/10 Taste - 10/10 Ambience - 8/10 Value - 10/10 Mind blasting factor - 10/10
